  "noticeDate": 1776398400000,
  "noticeDescription": "<p><strong>City's Residential Retrofit Program</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>PUBLIC NOTICE</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Notice of the imposition of special charges on benefitting properties under the City's Residential Retrofit Program.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Individual bills for each of the benefitting properties listed below have been submitted for the meeting of City Council being held on April 22, 23 and 24, 2026. Review bill details (<a href=\"https://secure.toronto.ca/council/bill-bylaw.do?meeting=2026.CC40\">https://secure.toronto.ca/council/bill-bylaw.do?meeting=2026.CC40</a>).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each of these bills imposes a special charge on each of the corresponding benefitting properties as a result of the property having entered into a Property Owner Agreement with the City and having undertaken energy efficiency and/or water conservation works as local improvements under the Residential Retrofit Program authorized by <a href=\"http://app.toronto.ca/tmmis/viewAgendaItemHistory.do?item=2013.EX33.22\">Executive Committee Item EX33.22, as adopted by Council on July 16, 17, 18 and 19, 2013</a> and enacted in <a href=\"http://www.toronto.ca/legdocs/bylaws/2013/law1105.pdf\">By-law 1105-2013 (July 19, 2013).</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The benefitting properties are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>3 Adelaide Place</li>\n<li>24 Bloomfield Avenue</li>\n<li>44 Highfield Road</li>\n<li>52 Austin Avenue</li>\n<li>56 Glenlake Avenue</li>\n<li>170 Elmhurst Drive</li>\n<li>1086 1/2 Queen Street West</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>For More Information Contact</strong></p>\n<p>City Council<br /><a href=\"mailto:councilmeeting@toronto.ca\">councilmeeting@toronto.ca</a></p>\n<p>Phone: 416-392-8485<br />Fax: 416-392-2980</p>\n<p>Toronto City Hall<br />100 Queen Street<br />Toronto, Ontario<br />M5H 2N2<br />Canada</p>",
